<doc id="453519" wikidata="Q1094772" url="?curid=453519" title="Clairaut's equation">
<text>In mathematical analysis, Clairaut&#x27;s equation (or the Clairaut equation) is a differential equation of the form

:formula_1

where formula_2 is continuously differentiable. It is a particular case of the Lagrange differential equation. It is named after the French mathematician Alexis Clairaut, who introduced it in 1734.

== Solution ==

To solve Clairaut&#x27;s equation, one differentiates with respect to formula_3, yielding

