or

:formula_7

In the former case, formula_8 for some constant formula_9. Substituting this into the Clairaut&#x27;s equation, one obtains the family of straight line functions given by

:formula_10

the so-called &quot;general solution&quot; of Clairaut&#x27;s equation.

The latter case,

:formula_11

defines only one solution formula_12, the so-called &quot;singular solution&quot;, whose graph is the envelope of the graphs of the general solutions. The singular solution is usually represented using parametric notation, as formula_13, where formula_14.

The parametric description of the singular solution has the form

